    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-28T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-28T23:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/587: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-29T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 29, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 29—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>428. Following from American Consul at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“May 28, noon. Chinese police on May 27th raided communistic meeting
                            attended by Soviet Consuls General, Harbin and Mukden, and held at local
                            Soviet Consulate General. About forty arrests made and consular premises
                            thoroughly searched.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
